{
  "texts": [
    "Now, if we can reduce the state space for sensor relations to its immediate neighbour actuators (a 1a 3 and a 7a 8; see dotted rectangle in Fig. 2), we reduce our solution seek time.",
    "Therefore, we employ a dimensionality reduction of the actuator(s) in relation with sensor s.Let there be normal and attack plant operation datasets for the sensor and actuator states logged during plant operations, under normal and attack conditions, respectively.",
    "A normal training dataset comprises of all seen (normal) state relations embedded into it.",
    "We implicitly rely on all actuator relations f (a 1, • • •, a 8) w.r.t.",
    "the sensor, but explicitly consider the actuation sequences for a 1 -a 3, for input side linearization."
  ]
}